often preserve aldonates rather than free sugars"}, "mechanism": "Partial oxidation converts glucose into more persistent sugar-acid reservoirs that may preserve hexose carbon skeletons under prebiotic conditions.", "reasoning": "The supplied report notes that aldonates are abundant in meteorites while canonical sugars are often absent, suggesting sugar acids may function as stable reservoirs. Furukawa et al. 2023 also showed borate-rich evaporative systems can phosphorylate gluconate analogously. This reaction contextualizes glucose persistence rather than claiming a primary synthetic route (Yi et al., 2023; Furukawa et al., 2023)."}], "pathways": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "name": "Cyanosulfidic to goethite-fructose to glucose", "description": "Best-supported terrestrial pathway: HCN photoredox chemistry yields glycolaldehyde and glyceraldehyde, then goethite catalyzes C3+C3 condensation to ketohexoses dominated by fructose, which equilibrates to glucose.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_010", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_009", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "name": "Extraterrestrial glycolaldehyde to goethite hexose route", "description": "Delivered glycolaldehyde enters terrestrial surface chemistry, is extended to glyceraldehyde through cyanosulfidic homologation, then condensed on goethite to fructose and isomerized to glucose.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_014", "rxn_002", "rxn_004", "rxn_010", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_008", "mol_009", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "Hydrothermal C1 feedstock to weak formose to glucose", "description": "Low-confidence route included only because the literature identifies vent-derived formaldehyde as a possible feeder and formose as the canonical historical network, despite strong selectivity and branching problems.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_005", "rxn_010", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_003", "mol_009", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Hydrothermal feedstock with borate-molybdate stepwise growth", "description": "Vent-derived formaldehyde seeds lower-sugar pools through weak formose chemistry, then borate/molybdate-guided tetrose-pentose growth and formaldehyde extension feed a ketohexose pool before fructose-glucose equilibration.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_005", "rxn_007", "rxn_011", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_003", "mol_011", "mol_012", "mol_015", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "name": "Cyanosulfidic lower-sugar growth to hexose extension route", "description": "HCN photochemistry supplies glycolaldehyde and glyceraldehyde, which enter borate/molybdate-guided tetrose/pentose growth and then C1 extension to the ketohexose pool before glucose formation.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_007", "rxn_011", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_008", "mol_009", "mol_011", "mol_012", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "name": "Glyoxylate-DHF pentose route plus C1 extension", "description": "Cleaner glyoxylate scenario: DHF reacts with glyceraldehyde to give pentose ketoses, which are extended with formaldehyde into a ketohexose pool and then equilibrated to glucose.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_008", "rxn_009", "rxn_011", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_014", "mol_012", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "name": "Cyanosulfidic plus glyoxylate convergent route", "description": "Cyanosulfidic chemistry supplies glyceraldehyde while the glyoxylate module supplies DHF; these converge to a pentose pool that is extended to ketohexoses and then to glucose.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_008", "rxn_009", "rxn_011", "rxn_013"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_014", "mol_012", "mol_016"]}, {"pathway_id": "P8", "name": "Extraterrestrial direct glucose delivery", "description": "Direct exogenous input of glucose from asteroid or meteoritic material supplies the target molecule without requir